The tetragnathid
Tetragnatha montana, commonly known as the silver stretch spider, was first described by Eugène Simon in 1874 and first recorded in the UK in 1895 (
British Arachnological Society, 2024;
Simon, 1874;
World Spider Catalog, 2024).
